info.title: Darena Health APIs
info.description: Darena Health APIs enable healthcare organizations to seamlessly connect with their FHIR APIs, ensuring compliance with the Cures Act/HTI-1 requirements and beyond.

get.summary:
Retrieves a specific page of a bundle in paged bundle scenarios: https://www.hl7.org/fhir/http.html#paging.
This endpoint does not have any parameters that can be defined by the user. The correct route with all required
information to this endpoint will be provided in Bundle.link.url

Starts a background job that processes one or more custom json files. A single json file can be given or a ZIP
file that contains a collection of json files can be given. If a ZIP file is given, the json must exist
in the root directory and cannot exist in any subdirectory. Subdirectories are ignored

parameters.name: patientOnly
parameters.description:
Optionally indicate if only the patient resource should be processed for each CCDA
            instead of all resources being processed. (Default: `false`)

parameters.name: emailForInvite
parameters.description: if provided, will send an email invite

get.summary:
Retrieves the patient's linked accounts in MeldRx. If the patient is linked to a person, the result model will
contain the person id and a status that will indicate that the patient is linked. The FHIR server id and patient
id will also be echoed back in the result model

parameters.name: fhirServerId
parameters.description:
The id of the FHIR server where the patient indicated by patientId
            exists

parameters.name: patientId
parameters.description: The id of the patient
